{"doc_id": "c3260077-d87f-5b81-96ec-08e6932b154d", "req_id": "REQ-158", "sent_id": "REQ-158::s120", "order": 120, "text": "## Error Taxonomy  \nErrors and warnings generated by the parser/analyzer are classified as follows:\n\n- **Syntax Errors:**", "is_candidate": false, "signals": {"action": true, "modal": false, "system": false, "constraint": false}}
{"doc_id": "c3260077-d87f-5b81-96ec-08e6932b154d", "req_id": "REQ-158", "sent_id": "REQ-158::s121", "order": 121, "text": "These are violations of the QASM grammar detected by the parser.", "is_candidate": false, "signals": {"action": false, "modal": false, "system": false, "constraint": false}}
{"doc_id": "c3260077-d87f-5b81-96ec-08e6932b154d", "req_id": "REQ-158", "sent_id": "REQ-158::s122", "order": 122, "text": "Examples include a missing semicolon, unmatched brackets, malformed `if` or `include` syntax, or using a keyword incorrectly.", "is_candidate": false, "signals": {"action": true, "modal": false, "system": false, "constraint": false}}
{"doc_id": "c3260077-d87f-5b81-96ec-08e6932b154d", "req_id": "REQ-158", "sent_id": "REQ-158::s123", "order": 123, "text": "A syntax error halts parsing and reports the offending line and expected tokens.", "is_candidate": false, "signals": {"action": true, "modal": false, "system": false, "constraint": false}}
{"doc_id": "c3260077-d87f-5b81-96ec-08e6932b154d", "req_id": "REQ-158", "sent_id": "REQ-158::s124", "order": 124, "text": "For instance, writing `qreg q[3]` without a semicolon would be a syntax error.", "is_candidate": false, "signals": {"action": false, "modal": false, "system": false, "constraint": false}}
{"doc_id": "c3260077-d87f-5b81-96ec-08e6932b154d", "req_id": "REQ-158", "sent_id": "REQ-158::s125", "order": 125, "text": "- **Semantic Errors:**", "is_candidate": false, "signals": {"action": false, "modal": false, "system": false, "constraint": false}}
{"doc_id": "c3260077-d87f-5b81-96ec-08e6932b154d", "req_id": "REQ-158", "sent_id": "REQ-158::s126", "order": 126, "text": "These occur after parsing, during symbol resolution and type checking.", "is_candidate": false, "signals": {"action": true, "modal": false, "system": false, "constraint": false}}
{"doc_id": "c3260077-d87f-5b81-96ec-08e6932b154d", "req_id": "REQ-158", "sent_id": "REQ-158::s127", "order": 127, "text": "They include using an undeclared register or gate, referencing an out-of-bounds index, duplicating a declaration name, or mismatching gate arity/types.", "is_candidate": false, "signals": {"action": true, "modal": false, "system": false, "constraint": false}}
{"doc_id": "c3260077-d87f-5b81-96ec-08e6932b154d", "req_id": "REQ-158", "sent_id": "REQ-158::s128", "order": 128, "text": "For example, calling `CX q[0], c[0]` (using a classical bit as a CX argument) or invoking a gate with too many parameters would be semantic errors.", "is_candidate": false, "signals": {"action": true, "modal": false, "system": false, "constraint": false}}
{"doc_id": "c3260077-d87f-5b81-96ec-08e6932b154d", "req_id": "REQ-158", "sent_id": "REQ-158::s130", "order": 130, "text": "Semantic errors prevent code generation or further analysis.", "is_candidate": false, "signals": {"action": true, "modal": false, "system": false, "constraint": false}}
{"doc_id": "c3260077-d87f-5b81-96ec-08e6932b154d", "req_id": "REQ-158", "sent_id": "REQ-158::s131", "order": 131, "text": "- **Logical (Design) Warnings:**", "is_candidate": false, "signals": {"action": false, "modal": false, "system": false, "constraint": false}}
{"doc_id": "c3260077-d87f-5b81-96ec-08e6932b154d", "req_id": "REQ-158", "sent_id": "REQ-158::s132", "order": 132, "text": "These are issues that do not violate syntax or basic semantics but likely indicate a logical flaw.", "is_candidate": false, "signals": {"action": true, "modal": false, "system": false, "constraint": false}}
{"doc_id": "c3260077-d87f-5b81-96ec-08e6932b154d", "req_id": "REQ-158", "sent_id": "REQ-158::s134", "order": 134, "text": "Another example is a constant condition in `if` that always skips or always executes a branch, which could indicate a mistake.", "is_candidate": false, "signals": {"action": true, "modal": false, "system": false, "constraint": false}}
{"doc_id": "c3260077-d87f-5b81-96ec-08e6932b154d", "req_id": "REQ-158", "sent_id": "REQ-158::s135", "order": 135, "text": "These do not stop compilation but are flagged to the user for review.", "is_candidate": false, "signals": {"action": true, "modal": false, "system": false, "constraint": false}}
{"doc_id": "c3260077-d87f-5b81-96ec-08e6932b154d", "req_id": "REQ-158", "sent_id": "REQ-158::s136", "order": 136, "text": "- **Runtime-Preventable Logical Errors:**", "is_candidate": false, "signals": {"action": false, "modal": false, "system": false, "constraint": false}}
{"doc_id": "c3260077-d87f-5b81-96ec-08e6932b154d", "req_id": "REQ-158", "sent_id": "REQ-158::s137", "order": 137, "text": "In the context of static analysis, we aim to catch as many potential bugs as possible before runtime.", "is_candidate": false, "signals": {"action": true, "modal": false, "system": false, "constraint": false}}
